      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; mesh convergence study required.",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted across three element sizes (coarse, medium, fine). Richardson extrapolation applied to stiffness and yield-force QoIs. GCI < 2.1% for all QoIs at the production mesh density. Discretization error contribution to total simulation uncertainty budget is 1.4%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver residuals converged to 1e-6 for all load steps. Nonlinear Newton-Raphson iterations converged within 15 substeps for the most demanding specimen. No solution divergence observed across 11 specimen simulations. Solver error estimated at <0.5% of QoI magnitude."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Simulation workflow executed by two independent analysts following a documented simulation plan. Results cross-checked between FDA and DePuy Synthes teams. Discrepancies >1% triggered mandatory review. No analyst-induced errors identified in final QoI outputs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic titanium alloy constitutive model with bilinear plasticity calibrated to Ti-6Al-4V coupon data. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) at screw-rod and screw-block interfaces validated against published tribology data. Model form uncertainty estimated via sensitivity analysis across plausible constitutive parameter ranges."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from certified mill certificates for each production lot. Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of each of the 11 test specimens (dimensional uncertainty <0.01 mm). Torque preload on set screws measured with calibrated torque wrench and applied in simulation. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (N=1000 runs)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from production lots, tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH and DePuy Synthes). Sample traceability documented to device history records. Coefficient of variation in experimental stiffness <6%, confirming adequate sample representativeness."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; multiple test configurations required.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending configuration only. Dynamic and fatigue loading conditions not included in this COU. Achieved level 2 (single standardized test condition) falls below required level 3. This shortfall is acknowledged; the COU scope is explicitly limited to static compression-bending and the acceptance decision is bounded accordingly."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Simulation boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry, displacement rate (5 mm/min quasi-static), and block spacing (44 mm) with documented fidelity. CMM-verified specimen geometry used as simulation input for each individual specimen, ensuring 1:1 correspondence between physical and virtual test articles."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; quantitative metric with uncertainty required.",
      "rationale": "QoI differences expressed as E/uval ratio per ASME V&V 40 Section 9. All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) yield E/uval < 1.96, satisfying the pre-established acceptance criterion. Validation uncertainty uval accounts for experimental measurement uncertainty, input parameter uncertainty, and numerical error."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Qualitative confirmation that simulated QoIs are directly linked to device safety and performance claims.",
      "rationale": "A thorough qualitative assessment was performed by the credibility assessment team to establish the relevance of the three selected quantities of interest — construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement — to the device's intended clinical function. These QoIs directly map to the mechanical performance claims in the 510(k) submission and are the standard metrics used by FDA reviewers for pedicle screw construct evaluation under ASTM F1717. The team reviewed the clinical literature on pedicle screw failure modes and confirmed that stiffness and yield force are the primary biomechanical determinants of construct integrity during post-operative loading. Given the direct regulatory and clinical alignment of these QoIs with the COU, the team concluded through structured expert elicitation that the QoI selection is fully appropriate and no additional scalar grading is necessary to convey the strength of this alignment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities directly replicate the COU loading scenario (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending) using production-equivalent hardware. The same FEA workflow, material models, and boundary conditions used in validation are applied in the regulatory submission context. Relevance is rated high; no significant gap exists between validation scenario and intended use scenario."
    }
  ],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed their required credibility levels. The single shortfall — Test conditions at achieved level 2 versus required level 3 — is acknowledged and bounded by the explicit COU restriction to static compression-bending only; no extrapolation to dynamic or fatigue regimes is claimed. The quantitative validation metric E/uval < 1.96 is satisfied for all three QoIs across N=11 specimens at two independent laboratories. The credibility assessment team unanimously concludes that the simulation evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim for this COU.",
